Authentication

bearerAuth

Security Scheme Type HTTP
HTTP Authorization Scheme bearer
Bearer format "JWT"

logoutFromCurrentSession

Takes a given refresh token and blacklists it.

  • Requires access token (isAuthenticated permission) passed with the request.
Authorizations:
bearerAuth
Request Body schema: application/json
refresh
required
string

Responses

main url for PRODUCTION USE

https://lockandrent.ru/api/v1/auth/logout/

main url for testing API

https://yuiborodin.xyz/api/v1/auth/logout/

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "refresh": "string"
}

Response samples

  • 400
Content type
application/json
{
  • "errors": [
    • {
      • "Bad Request": "Request was malformed or data was unacceptable. Try again with changed request."
      }
    ],
  • "status_code": 400
}

logoutFromAllSessions

Blacklists all tokens associated with the user that sent the request.

  • Requires access token (isAuthenticated permission) passed with the request.
Authorizations:
bearerAuth

Responses

main url for PRODUCTION USE

https://lockandrent.ru/api/v1/auth/logoutall/

main url for testing API

https://yuiborodin.xyz/api/v1/auth/logoutall/

Response samples

  • 400
Content type
application/json
{
  • "errors": [
    • {
      • "Bad Request": "Request was malformed or data was unacceptable. Try again with changed request."
      }
    ],
  • "status_code": 400
}

UserAPI.UserRelatedEntities

Endpoints for the related entites of the authenticated user such as bookings or organisations.

retrieveUserProperties


Retrieve a list of properties for the authenticated user. Note that a property will be listed if it's either been created by the authenticated user or the authenticated user has owner privileges (e.g. listed as property-owner, see properties:owners scope.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth

Responses

main url for PRODUCTION USE

https://lockandrent.ru/api/v1/user/properties/

main url for testing API

https://yuiborodin.xyz/api/v1/user/properties/

createProperty


This method is used for creating a property.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
Request Body schema: application/json
title
required
string <= 50 characters

Name of the property.

body
required
string <= 1024 characters

Description of the property

price
required
number <= 500000

Price of the property.

required
object (Availability)
active
boolean

Whether the property shows in search and list of all properties.

property_type
integer

Code for the type of the property.

booking_type
integer
Enum: 100 200

Code for the booking type of the property.

  • 100: Daily booking type
  • 200: Hourly booking type
visibility
integer
Enum: 100 150 200 250

Code for the visibility of the property.

  • 100: Publicly Visible
  • 150: Visible withing the organisation, if the property is connected to one.
  • 200: Visible only for owners.
  • 250: Visible withing property-group, if property is connected to one.
    If user chooses 150 or 250 codes and the property is not in an organsation or in a group then code 200 is used.
required
object (PropertyAddress)
client_greeting_message
string

Greeting message for clients from the owners.

requires_additional_confirmation
boolean

Whether the owner needs to approve bookings.

createPropertyBooking


Use this endpoint in order to create a booking for a particular property.
This endpoint could be used by any authenticated user. If the owner of the property doest the booking, the status is automatically set to ACCEPTED.
The AWAITING and DECLINED statuses are awailable only if the property has requires_additional_confirmation parameter set to true.

Note that if the booking is being created for the property with daily type of bookings then there's no need to provide the time and the timezone. Timezone offset is optional.

Cliend email is needed only if the owner creates the booking, otherwise the email of the current auth user is used.

Extended docs: Gitlab

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
path Parameters
properties:id
required
string

A unique integer value identifying the property.

Request Body schema: application/json
number_of_clients
required
integer [ 0 .. 1000 ]

Number of clients

client_email
string

This parameter is required only if the booking is being created by an owner.

booked_from
required
string
  • For DAILY bookings the accepted format is: 2020-12-17
  • For HOURLY bookings the accepted format is: 2020-12-17T03:00
    For HOURLY bookings the time in the property timezone must be used.
booked_until
required
string
  • For DAILY bookings the accepted format is: 2020-12-17
  • For HOURLY bookings the accepted format is: 2020-12-17T03:00
    For HOURLY bookings the time in the property timezone must be used.

Responses

main url for PRODUCTION USE

https://lockandrent.ru/api/v1/properties/{properties:id}/bookings/

main url for testing API

https://yuiborodin.xyz/api/v1/properties/{properties:id}/bookings/
